&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interested in feeding challenges and being a core member of a well established and recognised Head and Neck Team. This position is to cover a maternity leave until September 2021. It involves nutritionally caring for Head and Neck cancer inpatients and outpatients prior to, during and after their treatment working closely with an integrated MDT including specialist nurses, speech and language therapists and radiotherapists. This role involves supporting a band 5 dietitian on an oncology rotation and a dietetic support worker, delivering training to student dietitians completing A, B and C placements, medical students from the Exeter Medical School and other healthcare professionals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exiting opportunity for a motivated Dietitian to develop their skills in our friendly and supportive team an would make an excellent secondment opportunity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Exeter is a cathedral city close to the sea, lovely beaches and the ‘moors’. It offers a range of social and sporting activities and has good road and rail links to other parts of the UK.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hours: 30hrs/week( preferably available to work on Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays, however there is flexibility around the hours and days)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Salary: £31,365- 37,890 pro rata&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information contact Louisa Taylor Oncology Team Lead Dietitian on 01392 406237 or Catherine Tancock Nutrition and Dietetic Services Manager on 01392 403751.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;(This is a fixed term contract for 12 months.  For current NHS Employees this post could be a secondment opportunity) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are: &lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
